FRONTEND UPDATE — RMS task creation form
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Backend will now emit a form_widget event for RMS task creation.
Same rendering as the MRR form — no new component needed.

form_id: "rms_create_task_form"
Fields: employee_id (text), project_id (text), product_id (text),
        task_index (number), activity_index (number),
        start_date (date), end_date (date), planned_hours (number).

No conditional fields. No items table. All fields required.
No pre-filled defaults — user enters everything manually.

Submit payload (message = JSON.stringify):
{
    "action": "form_submit",
    "form_id": "rms_create_task_form",
    "data": {
        "employee_id": "3010",
        "project_id": "YEA2719",
        "product_id": "PRD001",
        "task_index": 1,
        "activity_index": 1,
        "start_date": "2026-06-10",
        "end_date": "2026-06-12",
        "planned_hours": 8
    }
}

form_errors events use the same format as MRR. Field keys:
employee_id, project_id, product_id, task_index, activity_index,
start_date, end_date, planned_hours.
